ek ke-ra-me-we, \\\"workers of ceramics\\\", written in Linear B syllabic script. The word \\\"ceramic\\\" may be used as an adjective to describe a material, product or process; or it maybe used as a noun, either singular, or more commonly, as the plural noun \\\"ceramics\\\".The earliest ceramics made by humans were pottery objects, including 27,000 year old figurines, made from clay, either by itself or mixed with other materials like silica, hardened, sintered, in fire. Later ceramics were glazed and fired to create smooth, colored surfaces, decreasing porosity through the use of glassy, amorphous ceramic coatings on top of the crystalline ceramic substrates. Ceramics now include domestic, industrial and building products, as well as a wide range of ceramic art. In the 20th century, new ceramic materials were developed for use in advanced ceramic engineering; for example (e.g. semiconductors).\",\"key\":\"Ceramic\"}],\"source\":{\"name\":\"维基百科\",\"url\":\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ceramic\"}},\"lang\":\"eng\",\"ec\":{\"exam_type\":[\"TOEFL\",\"GMAT\",\"IELTS\",\"CET6\",\"GRE\"],\"source\":{\"name\":\"有道词典\",\"url\":\"http://dict.youdao.com\"},\"word\":[{\"usphone\":\"səˈræmɪk\",\"ukphone\":\"səˈræmɪk\",\"ukspeech\":\"ceramic&type=1\",\"trs\":[{\"tr\":[{\"l\":{\"i\":[\"adj. 陶瓷的；陶器的；制陶艺术的\"]}}]},{\"tr\":[{\"l\":{\"i\":[\"n. 陶瓷；陶瓷制品\"]}}]}],\"wfs\":[{\"wf\":{\"name\":\"复数\",\"value\":\"ceramics\"}}],\"return-phrase\":{\"l\":{\"i\":\"ceramic\"}},\"usspeech\":\"ceramic&type=2\"}]},\"oxfordAdvance\":{\"encryptedData\":\"VOalywxKg51bjbWsBH44UtJ9CY2RsIDUpWweTc6e6X7rhuoKvqmbJMdcXES-sYcjtUMwoK54x78MUnAVqIUDvEhm8WVYpiM0dtkgjF-8FHESSXWdqDaFdrbzEPr_I_XzNT10yh9qETQktRtVTB1iAjTwtdjwmgmBBBC6FQXoMB9UAzcWC1rFLuP0ytd3jc1FE1dN8SF2RMNVlRtA3b6_TZRqEjpfWwG_nJdz48agq_H_2jBNlgVVtf7WxgP_dLNIet4pyNavEuP30uhBatTOnTzwAJX5Qgd-l6sfmTuxyDoxxkadOnZ1qMNUrq8I4EGeayYnc70PUN4yCBsM5wg4VDOACYIsgKreCmWE6MUsb0LI_7Fl0svQ2FyqkUpTM7LO4v9RrqWHHoWHUuw8wXhdEKut5Z25FF-gKoPrQMebQudta2NOHp7Kb08KbV3lnG50iAVl